title: Julie D wins Belmont feature in the slop
text:
Julie D wins Belmont feature in the slop AP 
Sep 30, 2015 at 5:55p ET + Updated Sep 30, 2015 at 5:55p ET 
NEW YORK (AP) Julie D held off Make the Moment by a neck in the slop Wednesday to take the $85,000 allowance feature for filly and mare sprinters at Belmont Park. 
Breaking from the rail, the 3-year-old trained by Jeremiah Englehart set the fractions to earn a third straight win. The time was 1:10.93 for the six furlongs. 
Julie D paid $15.60, $6.90 and $4.80. 
Make the Moment returned $5.20 and $3.80 while Angel Code, the 2-1 favorite, paid $2.80 to show.
